Taylor Holmes https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taylor_Holmes 0 Taylor Holmes (May 16, 1878 – September 30, 1959) was an actor who appeared in over 100 Broadway plays in his five-decade career. However, he is probably best remembered for his film roles, which he began in silent movies in 1917. In one of his earliest films, he starred in A Pair of Sixes (1918), produced by George K. Spoor.
